        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): prevent cross-turn tool-error banner suppression (#97849)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Reset `sawAssistantReply` when an assistant group has no reply text, marking agent-initiated turn boundaries that lack a user message.\n- Keeps failed cron/scheduled turns showing their Tool error banner instead of collapsing it when a later autonomous turn succeeds.\n\nFixes #97849\n\n## Root cause\n\n`annotateToolTurnOutcome` only reset `sawAssistantReply` at user groups. Back-to-back agent-initiated turns let a later assistant reply leak backward and stamp an earlier failed turn as `turnSucceeded=true`.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `cd ui && pnpm exec vitest run --config vitest.config.ts src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts` (51 passed)\n- [x] Existing #90122 / #89683 regression cases unchanged\n- [x] New cross-turn agent-initiated scenario with labeled empty assistant boundary\n\nMade with [Cursor](https://cursor.com)",
